-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Fri Mar 14, 2014 06:05AM EDT
-- None



March 14 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Friday:

** European buyout firm Charterhouse Capital Partners LLP is nearing a deal to acquire education software provider Skillsoft Ltd for more than $2 billion, people familiar with the matter said on Thursday. [ID:nL2N0MA2A3]  ** A Temasek-led shareholders group has offered to pay $2.1 billion in cash for the shares in Olam International Ltd <OLAM.SI> they do not already own, putting the heft of the Singapore state investor behind the commodity trading firm's weak balance sheet. [ID:nL3N0MA615]  ** Cable channel NuvoTV made a offer to buy Madison Square Garden Co's <MSG.O> Fuse TV for more than $200 million in cash and stock, Bloomberg reported citing people with knowledge of the matter. Jennifer Lopez-backed NuvoTV's offer pits the pop singer against former boyfriend Sean "Diddy" Combs, who made a bid of about $200 million for Fuse TV earlier this week, Bloomberg reported. (http://r.reuters.com/xuf67v) [ID:nL3N0MB2F8]  ** State-controlled Royal Bank of Scotland <RBS.L> has commissioned investment bank Morgan Stanley <MS.N> to advise it on potential merger opportunities for its Irish unit, Ulster Bank, the business's chief executive was quoted as saying. [ID:nL6N0MB0TO]  **  India's state-run Oil and Natural Gas Corp <ONGC.NS> and Oil India <OILI.NS> have completed the purchase of a 10 percent stake in state refiner Indian Oil Corp <IOC.NS> for 53.4 billion rupees ($873 million), senior executives at the two companies said. [ID:nL3N0MB2XJ]  ** Hong Kong property developer New World Development Co Ltd <0017.HK> said it would take its majority-owned New World China Land Ltd <0917.HK> unit private for HK$18.6 billion ($2.4 billion), seeking more flexibility in managing its flagship China-focused property business.[ID:nL3N0MB04H]  ** India is aiming to raise 30-40 billion rupees via the sale of a stake held by a state-run trust fund in Axis Bank <AXBK.NS> by month-end, Alok Tandon, joint secretary in the Department of Disinvestment said. [ID:nI8N0FO02I]  ** Spie has chosen six banks to run a stock market listing in Autumn that could value the French electrical and mechanical engineering group at 3 to 4 billion euros ($4.2-5.6 billion), Les Echos newspaper reported, citing sources. [ID:nL6N0MB0DX]  ** Carlyle Group <CG.O>, along with other investors, has agreed to acquire a majority stake in metals trader Traxys Group, in the latest move by the U.S. private equity firm to boost its presence in commodities as big banks scale back. [ID:nL3N0MB1PQ]  ** Africa-focused investor Emerging Capital Partners (ECP) is buying 33 percent of Atlas Bottling Corp, an Algerian firm which bottles PepsiCo Inc's <PEP.N> drinks, it said. ECP is buying the stake from Group Mehri, a prominent Algerian business family which owns Atlas, ECP said in a statement, without specifying how much it would spend on the acquisition. [ID:nL6N0MB0BP]  ** Bank Tabungan Pensiunan Nasional <BTPN.JK> shares surged after Japan's Sumitomo Mitsui Financial Group <8316.T> said it bought 919.3 million shares of the Indonesian lender. [ID:nL3N0MB2S2]  ** Liberty Media Corp <LMCA.O>, controlled by chairman John Malone, said it was no longer making an offer to buy all of Sirius XM's shares and announced plans to split its media holding company into two tracking stocks later this year. [ID:nL2N0MA2BI]  ** Chilean technology company Sonda SA <SON.SN> said on Thursday it had acquired Brazil-based information technology service provider CTIS for around $170 million, expanding its presence in Latin America's largest market. [ID:nL2N0MA2B9]  ($1 = 0.72 Euros) ($1 = 61.14 Rupees)